Ann Arbor Art Fair Update! Due to likely thunderstorms this afternoon, my chalk art demo at 200 E. Liberty has been rescheduled for Friday 7/21 and Saturday 7/22 from 1-3 pm. 

There will be chalk available for anyone who wants to create their own masterpieces in front of the post office, and my family will be selling my books, prints, postcards, the NEW 2024 calendar, and even a limited supply of mugs and tote bags that are currently not available anywhere else in the world! #streetarteverywhere #sidewalkchalk @annarborartfair

Adventures in Collaboration! I stumbled across an orderly line of blue rectangles outside an elementary school in my neighborhood, and with the help of two sisters waiting for their brother to finish soccer practice, we created an impressive parade of 15 dogs and one brave cat. 

Most of the creative credit goes to Clare and Nora, because I only scribbled in the blobs for legs, tail and head (and often forgot to draw a neck). All in all, an excellent reward for carrying chalk and charcoal everywhere I go! #streetart #sidewalkchalk #collaboration #bluedogs #inspiration #underfoot
